30/*!
31 \class QTreeView
32 \brief The QTreeView class provides a default model/view implementation of a tree view.
33
34 \ingroup model-view
35 \ingroup advanced
36 \inmodule QtWidgets
37
38 \image windows-treeview.png
39
40 A QTreeView implements a tree representation of items from a
41 model. This class is used to provide standard hierarchical lists that
42 were previously provided by the \c QListView class, but using the more
43 flexible approach provided by Qt's model/view architecture.
44
45 The QTreeView class is one of the \l{Model/View Classes} and is part of
46 Qt's \l{Model/View Programming}{model/view framework}.
47
48 QTreeView implements the interfaces defined by the
49 QAbstractItemView class to allow it to display data provided by
50 models derived from the QAbstractItemModel class.
51
52 It is simple to construct a tree view displaying data from a
53 model. In the following example, the contents of a directory are
54 supplied by a QFileSystemModel and displayed as a tree:
55
56 \snippet shareddirmodel/main.cpp 3
57 \snippet shareddirmodel/main.cpp 6
58
59 The model/view architecture ensures that the contents of the tree view
60 are updated as the model changes.
61
62 Items that have children can be in an expanded (children are
63 visible) or collapsed (children are hidden) state. When this state
64 changes a collapsed() or expanded() signal is emitted with the
65 model index of the relevant item.
66
67 The amount of indentation used to indicate levels of hierarchy is
68 controlled by the \l indentation property.
69
70 Headers in tree views are constructed using the QHeaderView class and can
71 be hidden using \c{header()->hide()}. Note that each header is configured
72 with its \l{QHeaderView::}{stretchLastSection} property set to true,
73 ensuring that the view does not waste any of the space assigned to it for
74 its header. If this value is set to true, this property will override the
75 resize mode set on the last section in the header.
76
77 By default, all columns in a tree view are movable except the first. To
78 disable movement of these columns, use QHeaderView's
79 \l {QHeaderView::}{setSectionsMovable()} function. For more information
80 about rearranging sections, see \l {Moving Header Sections}.
81
82 \section1 Key Bindings
83
84 QTreeView supports a set of key bindings that enable the user to
85 navigate in the view and interact with the contents of items:
86
87 \table
88 \header \li Key \li Action
89 \row \li Up \li Moves the cursor to the item in the same column on
90 the previous row. If the parent of the current item has no more rows to
91 navigate to, the cursor moves to the relevant item in the last row
92 of the sibling that precedes the parent.
93 \row \li Down \li Moves the cursor to the item in the same column on
94 the next row. If the parent of the current item has no more rows to
95 navigate to, the cursor moves to the relevant item in the first row
96 of the sibling that follows the parent.
97 \row \li Left \li Hides the children of the current item (if present)
98 by collapsing a branch.
99 \row \li Minus \li Same as Left.
100 \row \li Right \li Reveals the children of the current item (if present)
101 by expanding a branch.
102 \row \li Plus \li Same as Right.
103 \row \li Asterisk \li Expands the current item and all its children
104 (if present).
105 \row \li PageUp \li Moves the cursor up one page.
106 \row \li PageDown \li Moves the cursor down one page.
107 \row \li Home \li Moves the cursor to an item in the same column of the first
108 row of the first top-level item in the model.
109 \row \li End \li Moves the cursor to an item in the same column of the last
110 row of the last top-level item in the model.
111 \row \li F2 \li In editable models, this opens the current item for editing.
112 The Escape key can be used to cancel the editing process and revert
113 any changes to the data displayed.
114 \endtable
115
116 \omit
117 Describe the expanding/collapsing concept if not covered elsewhere.
118 \endomit
119
120 \section1 Improving Performance
121
122 It is possible to give the view hints about the data it is handling in order
123 to improve its performance when displaying large numbers of items. One approach
124 that can be taken for views that are intended to display items with equal heights
125 is to set the \l uniformRowHeights property to true.
126
127 \sa QListView, QTreeWidget, {View Classes}, QAbstractItemModel, QAbstractItemView,
128 {Dir View Example}
129*/
130

175/*!
176 \reimp
177*/
178void QTreeView::setModel(QAbstractItemModel *model)
179{
180 Q_D(QTreeView);
181 if (model == d->model)
182 return;
183 if (d->model && d->model != QAbstractItemModelPrivate::staticEmptyModel()) {
184 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
185 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
186
187 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelAboutToBeReset()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelAboutToBeReset()));
188 }
189
190 if (d->selectionModel) { // support row editing
191 disconnect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(currentRowChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
192 receiver: d->model, SLOT(submit()));
193 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
194 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
195 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelAboutToBeReset()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelAboutToBeReset()));
196 }
197 d->viewItems.clear();
198 d->expandedIndexes.clear();
199 d->hiddenIndexes.clear();
200 d->geometryRecursionBlock = true; // do not update geometries due to signals from the headers
201 d->header->setModel(model);
202 d->geometryRecursionBlock = false;
203 QAbstractItemView::setModel(model);
204
205 // QAbstractItemView connects to a private slot
206 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
207 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
208 // do header layout after the tree
209 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(layoutChanged()),
210 receiver: d->header, SLOT(_q_layoutChanged()));
211 // QTreeView has a public slot for this
212 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
213 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
214
215 connect(asender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelAboutToBeReset()), SLOT(_q_modelAboutToBeReset()));
216
217 if (d->sortingEnabled)
218 d->_q_sortIndicatorChanged(column: header()->sortIndicatorSection(), order: header()->sortIndicatorOrder());
219}

231/*!
232 \reimp
233*/
234void QTreeView::setSelectionModel(QItemSelectionModel *selectionModel)
235{
236 Q_D(QTreeView);
237 Q_ASSERT(selectionModel);
238 if (d->selectionModel) {
239 // support row editing
240 disconnect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(currentRowChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
241 receiver: d->model, SLOT(submit()));
242 }
243
244 d->header->setSelectionModel(selectionModel);
245 QAbstractItemView::setSelectionModel(selectionModel);
246
247 if (d->selectionModel) {
248 // support row editing
249 connect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(currentRowChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
250 receiver: d->model, SLOT(submit()));
251 }

261 Q_D(const QTreeView);

265/*!
266 Sets the header for the tree view, to the given \a header.
267
268 The view takes ownership over the given \a header and deletes it
269 when a new header is set.
270
271 \sa QAbstractItemModel::headerData()
272*/
273void QTreeView::setHeader(QHeaderView *header)
274{
275 Q_D(QTreeView);
276 if (header == d->header || !header)
277 return;
278 if (d->header && d->header->parent() == this)
279 delete d->header;
280 d->header = header;
281 d->header->setParent(this);
282 d->header->setFirstSectionMovable(false);
283
284 if (!d->header->model()) {
285 d->header->setModel(d->model);
286 if (d->selectionModel)
287 d->header->setSelectionModel(d->selectionModel);
288 }
289
290 connect(sender: d->header, SIGNAL(sectionResized(int,int,int)),
291 receiver: this, SLOT(columnResized(int,int,int)));
292 connect(sender: d->header, SIGNAL(sectionMoved(int,int,int)),
293 receiver: this, SLOT(columnMoved()));
294 connect(sender: d->header, SIGNAL(sectionCountChanged(int,int)),
295 receiver: this, SLOT(columnCountChanged(int,int)));
296 connect(sender: d->header, SIGNAL(sectionHandleDoubleClicked(int)),
297 receiver: this, SLOT(resizeColumnToContents(int)));
298 connect(sender: d->header, SIGNAL(geometriesChanged()),
299 receiver: this, SLOT(updateGeometries()));
300
301 setSortingEnabled(d->sortingEnabled);
302 d->updateGeometry();
303}

328/*!
329 \property QTreeView::indentation
330 \brief indentation of the items in the tree view.
331
332 This property holds the indentation measured in pixels of the items for each
333 level in the tree view. For top-level items, the indentation specifies the
334 horizontal distance from the viewport edge to the items in the first column;
335 for child items, it specifies their indentation from their parent items.
336
337 By default, the value of this property is style dependent. Thus, when the style
338 changes, this property updates from it. Calling setIndentation() stops the updates,
339 calling resetIndentation() will restore default behavior.
340*/
341int QTreeView::indentation() const
342{
343 Q_D(const QTreeView);
344 return d->indent;
345}
346
347void QTreeView::setIndentation(int i)
348{
349 Q_D(QTreeView);
350 if (!d->customIndent || (i != d->indent)) {
351 d->indent = i;
352 d->customIndent = true;
353 d->viewport->update();
354 }
355}
356
357void QTreeView::resetIndentation()
358{
359 Q_D(QTreeView);
360 if (d->customIndent) {
361 d->updateIndentationFromStyle();
362 d->customIndent = false;
363 }
364}

392/*!
393 \property QTreeView::uniformRowHeights
394 \brief whether all items in the treeview have the same height
395
396 This property should only be set to true if it is guaranteed that all items
397 in the view has the same height. This enables the view to do some
398 optimizations.
399
400 The height is obtained from the first item in the view. It is updated
401 when the data changes on that item.
402
403 \note If the editor size hint is bigger than the cell size hint, then the
404 size hint of the editor will be used.

406 By default, this property is \c false.
407*/

559bool QTreeView::isRowHidden(int row, const QModelIndex &parent) const

566
567/*!
568 If \a hide is true the \a row with the given \a parent is hidden, otherwise the \a row is shown.
569
570 \sa isRowHidden(), setColumnHidden()
571*/
572void QTreeView::setRowHidden(int row, const QModelIndex &parent, bool hide)
573{
574 Q_D(QTreeView);
575 if (!d->model)
576 return;
577 QModelIndex index = d->model->index(row, column: 0, parent);
578 if (!index.isValid())
579 return;
580
581 if (hide) {
582 d->hiddenIndexes.insert(value: index);
583 } else if (d->isPersistent(index)) { //if the index is not persistent, it cannot be in the set
584 d->hiddenIndexes.remove(value: index);
585 }
586
587 d->doDelayedItemsLayout();
588}
589
590/*!
591 \since 4.3
592
593 Returns \c true if the item in first column in the given \a row
594 of the \a parent is spanning all the columns; otherwise returns \c false.
595
596 \sa setFirstColumnSpanned()
597*/
598bool QTreeView::isFirstColumnSpanned(int row, const QModelIndex &parent) const
599{
600 Q_D(const QTreeView);
601 if (d->spanningIndexes.isEmpty() || !d->model)
602 return false;
603 const QModelIndex index = d->model->index(row, column: 0, parent);
604 return d->spanningIndexes.contains(value: index);
605}
606
607/*!
608 \since 4.3
609
610 If \a span is true the item in the first column in the \a row
611 with the given \a parent is set to span all columns, otherwise all items
612 on the \a row are shown.
613
614 \sa isFirstColumnSpanned()
615*/
616void QTreeView::setFirstColumnSpanned(int row, const QModelIndex &parent, bool span)
617{
618 Q_D(QTreeView);
619 if (!d->model)
620 return;
621 const QModelIndex index = d->model->index(row, column: 0, parent);
622 if (!index.isValid())
623 return;
624
625 if (span)
626 d->spanningIndexes.insert(value: index);
627 else
628 d->spanningIndexes.remove(value: index);
629
630 d->executePostedLayout();
631 int i = d->viewIndex(index);
632 if (i >= 0)
633 d->viewItems[i].spanning = span;
634
635 d->viewport->update();
636}

638/*!
639 \reimp
640*/
641void QTreeView::dataChanged(const QModelIndex &topLeft, const QModelIndex &bottomRight,
642 const QList<int> &roles)
643{
644 Q_D(QTreeView);
645
646 // if we are going to do a complete relayout anyway, there is no need to update
647 if (d->delayedPendingLayout)
648 return;
649
650 // refresh the height cache here; we don't really lose anything by getting the size hint,
651 // since QAbstractItemView::dataChanged() will get the visualRect for the items anyway
652
653 bool sizeChanged = false;
654 int topViewIndex = d->viewIndex(index: topLeft);
655 if (topViewIndex == 0) {
656 int newDefaultItemHeight = indexRowSizeHint(index: topLeft);
657 sizeChanged = d->defaultItemHeight != newDefaultItemHeight;
658 d->defaultItemHeight = newDefaultItemHeight;
659 }
660
661 if (topViewIndex != -1) {
662 if (topLeft.row() == bottomRight.row()) {
663 int oldHeight = d->itemHeight(item: topViewIndex);
664 d->invalidateHeightCache(item: topViewIndex);
665 sizeChanged |= (oldHeight != d->itemHeight(item: topViewIndex));
666 if (topLeft.column() == 0)
667 d->viewItems[topViewIndex].hasChildren = d->hasVisibleChildren(parent: topLeft);
668 } else {
669 int bottomViewIndex = d->viewIndex(index: bottomRight);
670 for (int i = topViewIndex; i <= bottomViewIndex; ++i) {
671 int oldHeight = d->itemHeight(item: i);
672 d->invalidateHeightCache(item: i);
673 sizeChanged |= (oldHeight != d->itemHeight(item: i));
674 if (topLeft.column() == 0)
675 d->viewItems[i].hasChildren = d->hasVisibleChildren(parent: d->viewItems.at(i).index);
676 }
677 }
678 }
679
680 if (sizeChanged) {
681 d->updateScrollBars();
682 d->viewport->update();
683 }
684 QAbstractItemView::dataChanged(topLeft, bottomRight, roles);
685}

719/*!
720 \fn void QTreeView::expand(const QModelIndex &index)
721
722 Expands the model item specified by the \a index.
723
724 \sa expanded()
725*/
726void QTreeView::expand(const QModelIndex &index)
727{
728 Q_D(QTreeView);
729 if (!d->isIndexValid(index))
730 return;
731 if (index.flags() & Qt::ItemNeverHasChildren)
732 return;
733 if (d->isIndexExpanded(idx: index))
734 return;
735 if (d->delayedPendingLayout) {
736 //A complete relayout is going to be performed, just store the expanded index, no need to layout.
737 if (d->storeExpanded(idx: index))
738 emit expanded(index);
739 return;
740 }
741
742 int i = d->viewIndex(index);
743 if (i != -1) { // is visible
744 d->expand(item: i, emitSignal: true);
745 if (!d->isAnimating()) {
746 updateGeometries();
747 d->viewport->update();
748 }
749 } else if (d->storeExpanded(idx: index)) {
750 emit expanded(index);
751 }
752}
753
754/*!
755 \fn void QTreeView::collapse(const QModelIndex &index)
756
757 Collapses the model item specified by the \a index.
758
759 \sa collapsed()
760*/
761void QTreeView::collapse(const QModelIndex &index)
762{
763 Q_D(QTreeView);
764 if (!d->isIndexValid(index))
765 return;
766 if (!d->isIndexExpanded(idx: index))
767 return;
768 //if the current item is now invisible, the autoscroll will expand the tree to see it, so disable the autoscroll
769 d->delayedAutoScroll.stop();
770
771 if (d->delayedPendingLayout) {
772 //A complete relayout is going to be performed, just un-store the expanded index, no need to layout.
773 if (d->isPersistent(index) && d->expandedIndexes.remove(value: index))
774 emit collapsed(index);
775 return;
776 }
777 int i = d->viewIndex(index);
778 if (i != -1) { // is visible
779 d->collapse(item: i, emitSignal: true);
780 if (!d->isAnimating()) {
781 updateGeometries();
782 viewport()->update();
783 }
784 } else {
785 if (d->isPersistent(index) && d->expandedIndexes.remove(value: index))
786 emit collapsed(index);
787 }
788}

968/*!
969 \reimp
970 */
971void QTreeView::keyboardSearch(const QString &search)
972{
973 Q_D(QTreeView);
974 if (!d->model->rowCount(parent: d->root) || !d->model->columnCount(parent: d->root))
975 return;
976
977 // Do a relayout nows, so that we can utilize viewItems
978 d->executePostedLayout();
979 if (d->viewItems.isEmpty())
980 return;
981
982 QModelIndex start;
983 if (currentIndex().isValid())
984 start = currentIndex();
985 else
986 start = d->viewItems.at(i: 0).index;
987
988 bool skipRow = false;
989 bool keyboardTimeWasValid = d->keyboardInputTime.isValid();
990 qint64 keyboardInputTimeElapsed;
991 if (keyboardTimeWasValid)
992 keyboardInputTimeElapsed = d->keyboardInputTime.restart();
993 else
994 d->keyboardInputTime.start();
995 if (search.isEmpty() || !keyboardTimeWasValid
996 || keyboardInputTimeElapsed > QApplication::keyboardInputInterval()) {
997 d->keyboardInput = search;
998 skipRow = currentIndex().isValid(); //if it is not valid we should really start at QModelIndex(0,0)
999 } else {
1000 d->keyboardInput += search;
1001 }
1002
1003 // special case for searches with same key like 'aaaaa'
1004 bool sameKey = false;
1005 if (d->keyboardInput.size() > 1) {
1006 int c = d->keyboardInput.count(c: d->keyboardInput.at(i: d->keyboardInput.size() - 1));
1007 sameKey = (c == d->keyboardInput.size());
1008 if (sameKey)
1009 skipRow = true;
1010 }
1011
1012 // skip if we are searching for the same key or a new search started
1013 if (skipRow) {
1014 if (indexBelow(index: start).isValid()) {
1015 start = indexBelow(index: start);
1016 } else {
1017 const int origCol = start.column();
1018 start = d->viewItems.at(i: 0).index;
1019 if (origCol != start.column())
1020 start = start.sibling(arow: start.row(), acolumn: origCol);
1021 }
1022 }
1023
1024 int startIndex = d->viewIndex(index: start);
1025 if (startIndex <= -1)
1026 return;
1027
1028 int previousLevel = -1;
1029 int bestAbove = -1;
1030 int bestBelow = -1;
1031 QString searchString = sameKey ? QString(d->keyboardInput.at(i: 0)) : d->keyboardInput;
1032 for (int i = 0; i < d->viewItems.size(); ++i) {
1033 if ((int)d->viewItems.at(i).level > previousLevel) {
1034 QModelIndex searchFrom = d->viewItems.at(i).index;
1035 if (start.column() > 0)
1036 searchFrom = searchFrom.sibling(arow: searchFrom.row(), acolumn: start.column());
1037 if (searchFrom.parent() == start.parent())
1038 searchFrom = start;
1039 QModelIndexList match = d->model->match(start: searchFrom, role: Qt::DisplayRole, value: searchString);
1040 if (match.size()) {
1041 int hitIndex = d->viewIndex(index: match.at(i: 0));
1042 if (hitIndex >= 0 && hitIndex < startIndex)
1043 bestAbove = bestAbove == -1 ? hitIndex : qMin(a: hitIndex, b: bestAbove);
1044 else if (hitIndex >= startIndex)
1045 bestBelow = bestBelow == -1 ? hitIndex : qMin(a: hitIndex, b: bestBelow);
1046 }
1047 }
1048 previousLevel = d->viewItems.at(i).level;
1049 }
1050
1051 QModelIndex index;
1052 if (bestBelow > -1)
1053 index = d->viewItems.at(i: bestBelow).index;
1054 else if (bestAbove > -1)
1055 index = d->viewItems.at(i: bestAbove).index;
1056
1057 if (start.column() > 0)
1058 index = index.sibling(arow: index.row(), acolumn: start.column());
1059
1060 if (index.isValid())
1061 setCurrentIndex(index);
1062}
1063
1064/*!
1065 Returns the rectangle on the viewport occupied by the item at \a index.
1066 If the index is not visible or explicitly hidden, the returned rectangle is invalid.
1067*/
1068QRect QTreeView::visualRect(const QModelIndex &index) const
1069{
1070 Q_D(const QTreeView);
1071
1072 if (!d->isIndexValid(index) || isIndexHidden(index))
1073 return QRect();
1074
1075 d->executePostedLayout();
1076
1077 int vi = d->viewIndex(index);
1078 if (vi < 0)
1079 return QRect();
1080
1081 bool spanning = d->viewItems.at(i: vi).spanning;
1082
1083 // if we have a spanning item, make the selection stretch from left to right
1084 int x = (spanning ? 0 : columnViewportPosition(column: index.column()));
1085 int w = (spanning ? d->header->length() : columnWidth(column: index.column()));
1086 // handle indentation
1087 if (d->isTreePosition(logicalIndex: index.column())) {
1088 int i = d->indentationForItem(item: vi);
1089 w -= i;
1090 if (!isRightToLeft())
1091 x += i;
1092 }
1093
1094 int y = d->coordinateForItem(item: vi);
1095 int h = d->itemHeight(item: vi);
1096
1097 return QRect(x, y, w, h);
1098}

1100/*!
1101 Scroll the contents of the tree view until the given model item
1102 \a index is visible. The \a hint parameter specifies more
1103 precisely where the item should be located after the
1104 operation.
1105 If any of the parents of the model item are collapsed, they will
1106 be expanded to ensure that the model item is visible.
1107*/
1108void QTreeView::scrollTo(const QModelIndex &index, ScrollHint hint)
1109{
1110 Q_D(QTreeView);
1111
1112 if (!d->isIndexValid(index))
1113 return;
1114
1115 d->executePostedLayout();
1116 d->updateScrollBars();
1117
1118 // Expand all parents if the parent(s) of the node are not expanded.
1119 QModelIndex parent = index.parent();
1120 while (parent != d->root && parent.isValid() && state() == NoState && d->itemsExpandable) {
1121 if (!isExpanded(index: parent))
1122 expand(index: parent);
1123 parent = d->model->parent(child: parent);
1124 }
1125
1126 int item = d->viewIndex(index);
1127 if (item < 0)
1128 return;
1129
1130 QRect area = d->viewport->rect();
1131
1132 // vertical
1133 if (verticalScrollMode() == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerItem) {
1134 int top = verticalScrollBar()->value();
1135 int bottom = top + verticalScrollBar()->pageStep();
1136 if (hint == EnsureVisible && item >= top && item < bottom) {
1137 // nothing to do
1138 } else if (hint == PositionAtTop || (hint == EnsureVisible && item < top)) {
1139 verticalScrollBar()->setValue(item);
1140 } else { // PositionAtBottom or PositionAtCenter
1141 const int currentItemHeight = d->itemHeight(item);
1142 int y = (hint == PositionAtCenter
1143 //we center on the current item with a preference to the top item (ie. -1)
1144 ? area.height() / 2 + currentItemHeight - 1
1145 //otherwise we simply take the whole space
1146 : area.height());
1147 if (y > currentItemHeight) {
1148 while (item >= 0) {
1149 y -= d->itemHeight(item);
1150 if (y < 0) { //there is no more space left
1151 item++;
1152 break;
1153 }
1154 item--;
1155 }
1156 }
1157 verticalScrollBar()->setValue(item);
1158 }
1159 } else { // ScrollPerPixel
1160 QRect rect(columnViewportPosition(column: index.column()),
1161 d->coordinateForItem(item), // ### slow for items outside the view
1162 columnWidth(column: index.column()),
1163 d->itemHeight(item));
1164
1165 if (rect.isEmpty()) {
1166 // nothing to do
1167 } else if (hint == EnsureVisible && area.contains(r: rect)) {
1168 d->viewport->update(rect);
1169 // nothing to do
1170 } else {
1171 bool above = (hint == EnsureVisible
1172 && (rect.top() < area.top()
1173 || area.height() < rect.height()));
1174 bool below = (hint == EnsureVisible
1175 && rect.bottom() > area.bottom()
1176 && rect.height() < area.height());
1177
1178 int verticalValue = verticalScrollBar()->value();
1179 if (hint == PositionAtTop || above)
1180 verticalValue += rect.top();
1181 else if (hint == PositionAtBottom || below)
1182 verticalValue += rect.bottom() - area.height();
1183 else if (hint == PositionAtCenter)
1184 verticalValue += rect.top() - ((area.height() - rect.height()) / 2);
1185 verticalScrollBar()->setValue(verticalValue);
1186 }
1187 }
1188 // horizontal
1189 int viewportWidth = d->viewport->width();
1190 int horizontalOffset = d->header->offset();
1191 int horizontalPosition = d->header->sectionPosition(logicalIndex: index.column());
1192 int cellWidth = d->header->sectionSize(logicalIndex: index.column());
1193
1194 if (hint == PositionAtCenter) {
1195 horizontalScrollBar()->setValue(horizontalPosition - ((viewportWidth - cellWidth) / 2));
1196 } else {
1197 if (horizontalPosition - horizontalOffset < 0 || cellWidth > viewportWidth)
1198 horizontalScrollBar()->setValue(horizontalPosition);
1199 else if (horizontalPosition - horizontalOffset + cellWidth > viewportWidth)
1200 horizontalScrollBar()->setValue(horizontalPosition - viewportWidth + cellWidth);
1201 }
1202}

1220/*!
1221 \reimp
1222*/
1223void QTreeView::timerEvent(QTimerEvent *event)
1224{
1225 Q_D(QTreeView);
1226 if (event->timerId() == d->columnResizeTimerID) {
1227 updateGeometries();
1228 killTimer(id: d->columnResizeTimerID);
1229 d->columnResizeTimerID = 0;
1230 QRect rect;
1231 int viewportHeight = d->viewport->height();
1232 int viewportWidth = d->viewport->width();
1233 for (int i = d->columnsToUpdate.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1234 int column = d->columnsToUpdate.at(i);
1235 int x = columnViewportPosition(column);
1236 if (isRightToLeft())
1237 rect |= QRect(0, 0, x + columnWidth(column), viewportHeight);
1238 else
1239 rect |= QRect(x, 0, viewportWidth - x, viewportHeight);
1240 }
1241 d->viewport->update(rect.normalized());
1242 d->columnsToUpdate.clear();
1243 } else if (event->timerId() == d->openTimer.timerId()) {
1244 QPoint pos = d->viewport->mapFromGlobal(QCursor::pos());
1245 if (state() == QAbstractItemView::DraggingState
1246 && d->viewport->rect().contains(p: pos)) {
1247 QModelIndex index = indexAt(p: pos);
1248 setExpanded(index, expanded: !isExpanded(index));
1249 }
1250 d->openTimer.stop();
1251 }
1252
1253 QAbstractItemView::timerEvent(event);
1254}

1269/*!
1270 \reimp
1271*/
1272bool QTreeView::viewportEvent(QEvent *event)
1273{
1274 Q_D(QTreeView);
1275 switch (event->type()) {
1276 case QEvent::HoverEnter:
1277 case QEvent::HoverLeave:
1278 case QEvent::HoverMove: {
1279 QHoverEvent *he = static_cast<QHoverEvent*>(event);
1280 int oldBranch = d->hoverBranch;
1281 d->hoverBranch = d->itemDecorationAt(pos: he->position().toPoint());
1282 QModelIndex newIndex = indexAt(p: he->position().toPoint());
1283 if (d->hover != newIndex || d->hoverBranch != oldBranch) {
1284 // Update the whole hovered over row. No need to update the old hovered
1285 // row, that is taken care in superclass hover handling.
1286 QRect rect = visualRect(index: newIndex);
1287 rect.setX(0);
1288 rect.setWidth(viewport()->width());
1289 viewport()->update(rect);
1290 }
1291 break; }
1292 default:
1293 break;
1294 }
1295 return QAbstractItemView::viewportEvent(event);
1296}

1328void QTreeViewPrivate::paintAlternatingRowColors(QPainter *painter, QStyleOptionViewItem *option, int y, int bottom) const
1329{
1330 Q_Q(const QTreeView);
1331 if (!alternatingColors || !q->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_PaintAlternatingRowColorsForEmptyArea, opt: option, widget: q))
1332 return;
1333 int rowHeight = defaultItemHeight;
1334 if (rowHeight <= 0) {
1335 rowHeight = itemDelegate->sizeHint(option: *option, index: QModelIndex()).height();
1336 if (rowHeight <= 0)
1337 return;
1338 }
1339 while (y <= bottom) {
1340 option->rect.setRect(ax: 0, ay: y, aw: viewport->width(), ah: rowHeight);
1341 option->features.setFlag(flag: QStyleOptionViewItem::Alternate, on: current & 1);
1342 ++current;
1343 q->style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_PanelItemViewRow, opt: option, p: painter, w: q);
1344 y += rowHeight;
1345 }
1346}
1347
1348bool QTreeViewPrivate::expandOrCollapseItemAtPos(const QPoint &pos)
1349{
1350 Q_Q(QTreeView);
1351 // we want to handle mousePress in EditingState (persistent editors)
1352 if ((state != QAbstractItemView::NoState
1353 && state != QAbstractItemView::EditingState)
1354 || !viewport->rect().contains(p: pos))
1355 return true;
1356
1357 int i = itemDecorationAt(pos);
1358 if ((i != -1) && itemsExpandable && hasVisibleChildren(parent: viewItems.at(i).index)) {
1359 if (viewItems.at(i).expanded)
1360 collapse(item: i, emitSignal: true);
1361 else
1362 expand(item: i, emitSignal: true);
1363 if (!isAnimating()) {
1364 q->updateGeometries();
1365 viewport->update();
1366 }
1367 return true;
1368 }
1369 return false;
1370}

1380QRect QTreeViewPrivate::intersectedRect(const QRect rect, const QModelIndex &topLeft, const QModelIndex &bottomRight) const
1381{
1382 Q_Q(const QTreeView);
1383
1384 const auto parentIdx = topLeft.parent();
1385 executePostedLayout();
1386 QRect updateRect;
1387 for (int r = topLeft.row(); r <= bottomRight.row(); ++r) {
1388 if (isRowHidden(idx: model->index(row: r, column: 0, parent: parentIdx)))
1389 continue;
1390 for (int c = topLeft.column(); c <= bottomRight.column(); ++c) {
1391 const QModelIndex idx(model->index(row: r, column: c, parent: parentIdx));
1392 updateRect |= q->visualRect(index: idx);
1393 }
1394 }
1395 return rect.intersected(other: updateRect);
1396}

1418void QTreeViewPrivate::adjustViewOptionsForIndex(QStyleOptionViewItem *option, const QModelIndex &current) const
1419{
1420 const int row = viewIndex(index: current); // get the index in viewItems[]
1421 option->state = option->state | (viewItems.at(i: row).expanded ? QStyle::State_Open : QStyle::State_None)
1422 | (viewItems.at(i: row).hasChildren ? QStyle::State_Children : QStyle::State_None)
1423 | (viewItems.at(i: row).hasMoreSiblings ? QStyle::State_Sibling : QStyle::State_None);
1424
1425 option->showDecorationSelected = (selectionBehavior & QTreeView::SelectRows)
1426 || option->showDecorationSelected;
1427
1428 QList<int>
1429 logicalIndices; // index = visual index of visible columns only. data = logical index.
1430 QList<QStyleOptionViewItem::ViewItemPosition>
1431 viewItemPosList; // vector of left/middle/end for each logicalIndex, visible columns
1432 // only.
1433 const bool spanning = viewItems.at(i: row).spanning;
1434 const int left = (spanning ? header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: 0) : 0);
1435 const int right = (spanning ? header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: 0) : header->count() - 1 );
1436 calcLogicalIndices(logicalIndices: &logicalIndices, itemPositions: &viewItemPosList, left, right);
1437
1438 const int visualIndex = logicalIndices.indexOf(t: current.column());
1439 option->viewItemPosition = viewItemPosList.at(i: visualIndex);
1440}

1442
1443/*!
1444 \since 4.2
1445 Draws the part of the tree intersecting the given \a region using the specified
1446 \a painter.
1447
1448 \sa paintEvent()
1449*/
1450void QTreeView::drawTree(QPainter *painter, const QRegion &region) const
1451{
1452 Q_D(const QTreeView);
1453 // d->viewItems changes when posted layouts are executed in itemDecorationAt, so don't copy
1454 const QList<QTreeViewItem> &viewItems = d->viewItems;
1455
1456 QStyleOptionViewItem option;
1457 initViewItemOption(option: &option);
1458 const QStyle::State state = option.state;
1459 d->current = 0;
1460
1461 if (viewItems.size() == 0 || d->header->count() == 0 || !d->itemDelegate) {
1462 d->paintAlternatingRowColors(painter, option: &option, y: 0, bottom: region.boundingRect().bottom()+1);
1463 return;
1464 }
1465
1466 int firstVisibleItemOffset = 0;
1467 const int firstVisibleItem = d->firstVisibleItem(offset: &firstVisibleItemOffset);
1468 if (firstVisibleItem < 0) {
1469 d->paintAlternatingRowColors(painter, option: &option, y: 0, bottom: region.boundingRect().bottom()+1);
1470 return;
1471 }
1472
1473 const int viewportWidth = d->viewport->width();
1474
1475 QPoint hoverPos = d->viewport->mapFromGlobal(QCursor::pos());
1476 d->hoverBranch = d->itemDecorationAt(pos: hoverPos);
1477
1478 QList<int> drawn;
1479 bool multipleRects = (region.rectCount() > 1);
1480 for (const QRect &a : region) {
1481 const QRect area = (multipleRects
1482 ? QRect(0, a.y(), viewportWidth, a.height())
1483 : a);
1484 d->leftAndRight = d->startAndEndColumns(rect: area);
1485
1486 int i = firstVisibleItem; // the first item at the top of the viewport
1487 int y = firstVisibleItemOffset; // we may only see part of the first item
1488
1489 // start at the top of the viewport and iterate down to the update area
1490 for (; i < viewItems.size(); ++i) {
1491 const int itemHeight = d->itemHeight(item: i);
1492 if (y + itemHeight > area.top())
1493 break;
1494 y += itemHeight;
1495 }
1496
1497 // paint the visible rows
1498 for (; i < viewItems.size() && y <= area.bottom(); ++i) {
1499 const int itemHeight = d->itemHeight(item: i);
1500 option.rect.setRect(ax: 0, ay: y, aw: viewportWidth, ah: itemHeight);
1501 option.state = state | (viewItems.at(i).expanded ? QStyle::State_Open : QStyle::State_None)
1502 | (viewItems.at(i).hasChildren ? QStyle::State_Children : QStyle::State_None)
1503 | (viewItems.at(i).hasMoreSiblings ? QStyle::State_Sibling : QStyle::State_None);
1504 d->current = i;
1505 d->spanning = viewItems.at(i).spanning;
1506 if (!multipleRects || !drawn.contains(t: i)) {
1507 drawRow(painter, options: option, index: viewItems.at(i).index);
1508 if (multipleRects) // even if the rect only intersects the item,
1509 drawn.append(t: i); // the entire item will be painted
1510 }
1511 y += itemHeight;
1512 }
1513
1514 if (y <= area.bottom()) {
1515 d->current = i;
1516 d->paintAlternatingRowColors(painter, option: &option, y, bottom: area.bottom());
1517 }
1518 }
1519}

1521/// ### move to QObject :)
1522static inline bool ancestorOf(QObject *widget, QObject *other)
1523{
1524 for (QObject *parent = other; parent != nullptr; parent = parent->parent()) {
1525 if (parent == widget)
1526 return true;
1527 }
1528 return false;
1529}
1530
1531void QTreeViewPrivate::calcLogicalIndices(
1532 QList<int> *logicalIndices, QList<QStyleOptionViewItem::ViewItemPosition> *itemPositions,
1533 int left, int right) const
1534{
1535 const int columnCount = header->count();
1536 /* 'left' and 'right' are the left-most and right-most visible visual indices.
1537 Compute the first visible logical indices before and after the left and right.
1538 We will use these values to determine the QStyleOptionViewItem::viewItemPosition. */
1539 int logicalIndexBeforeLeft = -1, logicalIndexAfterRight = -1;
1540 for (int visualIndex = left - 1; visualIndex >= 0; --visualIndex) {
1541 int logicalIndex = header->logicalIndex(visualIndex);
1542 if (!header->isSectionHidden(logicalIndex)) {
1543 logicalIndexBeforeLeft = logicalIndex;
1544 break;
1545 }
1546 }
1547
1548 for (int visualIndex = left; visualIndex < columnCount; ++visualIndex) {
1549 int logicalIndex = header->logicalIndex(visualIndex);
1550 if (!header->isSectionHidden(logicalIndex)) {
1551 if (visualIndex > right) {
1552 logicalIndexAfterRight = logicalIndex;
1553 break;
1554 }
1555 logicalIndices->append(t: logicalIndex);
1556 }
1557 }
1558
1559 itemPositions->resize(size: logicalIndices->size());
1560 for (int currentLogicalSection = 0; currentLogicalSection < logicalIndices->size(); ++currentLogicalSection) {
1561 const int headerSection = logicalIndices->at(i: currentLogicalSection);
1562 // determine the viewItemPosition depending on the position of column 0
1563 int nextLogicalSection = currentLogicalSection + 1 >= logicalIndices->size()
1564 ? logicalIndexAfterRight
1565 : logicalIndices->at(i: currentLogicalSection + 1);
1566 int prevLogicalSection = currentLogicalSection - 1 < 0
1567 ? logicalIndexBeforeLeft
1568 : logicalIndices->at(i: currentLogicalSection - 1);
1569 QStyleOptionViewItem::ViewItemPosition pos;
1570 if (columnCount == 1 || (nextLogicalSection == 0 && prevLogicalSection == -1)
1571 || (headerSection == 0 && nextLogicalSection == -1) || spanning)
1572 pos = QStyleOptionViewItem::OnlyOne;
1573 else if (isTreePosition(logicalIndex: headerSection) || (nextLogicalSection != 0 && prevLogicalSection == -1))
1574 pos = QStyleOptionViewItem::Beginning;
1575 else if (nextLogicalSection == 0 || nextLogicalSection == -1)
1576 pos = QStyleOptionViewItem::End;
1577 else
1578 pos = QStyleOptionViewItem::Middle;
1579 (*itemPositions)[currentLogicalSection] = pos;
1580 }
1581}
1582
1583/*!
1584 \internal
1585 Get sizeHint width for single index (providing existing hint and style option) and index in viewIndex i.
1586*/
1587int QTreeViewPrivate::widthHintForIndex(const QModelIndex &index, int hint, const QStyleOptionViewItem &option, int i) const
1588{
1589 Q_Q(const QTreeView);
1590 QWidget *editor = editorForIndex(index).widget.data();
1591 if (editor && persistent.contains(value: editor)) {
1592 hint = qMax(a: hint, b: editor->sizeHint().width());
1593 int min = editor->minimumSize().width();
1594 int max = editor->maximumSize().width();
1595 hint = qBound(min, val: hint, max);
1596 }
1597 int xhint = q->itemDelegateForIndex(index)->sizeHint(option, index).width();
1598 hint = qMax(a: hint, b: xhint + (isTreePosition(logicalIndex: index.column()) ? indentationForItem(item: i) : 0));
1599 return hint;
1600}
1601
1602/*!
1603 Draws the row in the tree view that contains the model item \a index,
1604 using the \a painter given. The \a option controls how the item is
1605 displayed.
1606
1607 \sa setAlternatingRowColors()
1608*/
1609void QTreeView::drawRow(QPainter *painter, const QStyleOptionViewItem &option,
1610 const QModelIndex &index) const
1611{
1612 Q_D(const QTreeView);
1613 QStyleOptionViewItem opt = option;
1614 const QPoint offset = d->scrollDelayOffset;
1615 const int y = option.rect.y() + offset.y();
1616 const QModelIndex parent = index.parent();
1617 const QHeaderView *header = d->header;
1618 const QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
1619 const QModelIndex hover = d->hover;
1620 const bool reverse = isRightToLeft();
1621 const QStyle::State state = opt.state;
1622 const bool spanning = d->spanning;
1623 const int left = (spanning ? header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: 0) : d->leftAndRight.first);
1624 const int right = (spanning ? header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: 0) : d->leftAndRight.second);
1625 const bool alternate = d->alternatingColors;
1626 const bool enabled = (state & QStyle::State_Enabled) != 0;
1627 const bool allColumnsShowFocus = d->allColumnsShowFocus;
1628
1629
1630 // when the row contains an index widget which has focus,
1631 // we want to paint the entire row as active
1632 bool indexWidgetHasFocus = false;
1633 if ((current.row() == index.row()) && !d->editorIndexHash.isEmpty()) {
1634 const int r = index.row();
1635 QWidget *fw = QApplication::focusWidget();
1636 for (int c = 0; c < header->count(); ++c) {
1637 QModelIndex idx = d->model->index(row: r, column: c, parent);
1638 if (QWidget *editor = indexWidget(index: idx)) {
1639 if (ancestorOf(widget: editor, other: fw)) {
1640 indexWidgetHasFocus = true;
1641 break;
1642 }
1643 }
1644 }
1645 }
1646
1647 const bool widgetHasFocus = hasFocus();
1648 bool currentRowHasFocus = false;
1649 if (allColumnsShowFocus && widgetHasFocus && current.isValid()) {
1650 // check if the focus index is before or after the visible columns
1651 const int r = index.row();
1652 for (int c = 0; c < left && !currentRowHasFocus; ++c) {
1653 QModelIndex idx = d->model->index(row: r, column: c, parent);
1654 currentRowHasFocus = (idx == current);
1655 }
1656 QModelIndex parent = d->model->parent(child: index);
1657 for (int c = right; c < header->count() && !currentRowHasFocus; ++c) {
1658 currentRowHasFocus = (d->model->index(row: r, column: c, parent) == current);
1659 }
1660 }
1661
1662 // ### special case: if we select entire rows, then we need to draw the
1663 // selection in the first column all the way to the second column, rather
1664 // than just around the item text. We abuse showDecorationSelected to
1665 // indicate this to the style. Below we will reset this value temporarily
1666 // to only respect the styleHint while we are rendering the decoration.
1667 opt.showDecorationSelected = (d->selectionBehavior & SelectRows)
1668 || option.showDecorationSelected;
1669
1670 int width, height = option.rect.height();
1671 int position;
1672 QModelIndex modelIndex;
1673 const bool hoverRow = selectionBehavior() == QAbstractItemView::SelectRows
1674 && index.parent() == hover.parent()
1675 && index.row() == hover.row();
1676
1677 QList<int> logicalIndices;
1678 QList<QStyleOptionViewItem::ViewItemPosition>
1679 viewItemPosList; // vector of left/middle/end for each logicalIndex
1680 d->calcLogicalIndices(logicalIndices: &logicalIndices, itemPositions: &viewItemPosList, left, right);
1681
1682 for (int currentLogicalSection = 0; currentLogicalSection < logicalIndices.size(); ++currentLogicalSection) {
1683 int headerSection = logicalIndices.at(i: currentLogicalSection);
1684 position = columnViewportPosition(column: headerSection) + offset.x();
1685 width = header->sectionSize(logicalIndex: headerSection);
1686
1687 if (spanning) {
1688 int lastSection = header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: header->count() - 1);
1689 if (!reverse) {
1690 width = columnViewportPosition(column: lastSection) + header->sectionSize(logicalIndex: lastSection) - position;
1691 } else {
1692 width += position - columnViewportPosition(column: lastSection);
1693 position = columnViewportPosition(column: lastSection);
1694 }
1695 }
1696
1697 modelIndex = d->model->index(row: index.row(), column: headerSection, parent);
1698 if (!modelIndex.isValid())
1699 continue;
1700 opt.state = state;
1701
1702 opt.viewItemPosition = viewItemPosList.at(i: currentLogicalSection);
1703
1704 // fake activeness when row editor has focus
1705 if (indexWidgetHasFocus)
1706 opt.state |= QStyle::State_Active;
1707
1708 if (d->selectionModel->isSelected(index: modelIndex))
1709 opt.state |= QStyle::State_Selected;
1710 if (widgetHasFocus && (current == modelIndex)) {
1711 if (allColumnsShowFocus)
1712 currentRowHasFocus = true;
1713 else
1714 opt.state |= QStyle::State_HasFocus;
1715 }
1716 opt.state.setFlag(flag: QStyle::State_MouseOver,
1717 on: (hoverRow || modelIndex == hover)
1718 && (option.showDecorationSelected || d->hoverBranch == -1));
1719
1720 if (enabled) {
1721 QPalette::ColorGroup cg;
1722 if ((d->model->flags(index: modelIndex) & Qt::ItemIsEnabled) == 0) {
1723 opt.state &= ~QStyle::State_Enabled;
1724 cg = QPalette::Disabled;
1725 } else if (opt.state & QStyle::State_Active) {
1726 cg = QPalette::Active;
1727 } else {
1728 cg = QPalette::Inactive;
1729 }
1730 opt.palette.setCurrentColorGroup(cg);
1731 }
1732
1733 if (alternate) {
1734 opt.features.setFlag(flag: QStyleOptionViewItem::Alternate, on: d->current & 1);
1735 }
1736
1737 /* Prior to Qt 4.3, the background of the branch (in selected state and
1738 alternate row color was provided by the view. For backward compatibility,
1739 this is now delegated to the style using PE_PanelItemViewRow which
1740 does the appropriate fill */
1741 if (d->isTreePosition(logicalIndex: headerSection)) {
1742 const int i = d->indentationForItem(item: d->current);
1743 QRect branches(reverse ? position + width - i : position, y, i, height);
1744 const bool setClipRect = branches.width() > width;
1745 if (setClipRect) {
1746 painter->save();
1747 painter->setClipRect(QRect(position, y, width, height));
1748 }
1749 // draw background for the branch (selection + alternate row)
1750 opt.rect = branches;
1751
1752 // We use showDecorationSelected both to store the style hint, and to indicate
1753 // that the entire row has to be selected (see overrides of the value if
1754 // selectionBehavior == SelectRow).
1755 // While we are only painting the background we don't care for the
1756 // selectionBehavior factor, so respect only the style value, and reset later.
1757 const bool oldShowDecorationSelected = opt.showDecorationSelected;
1758 opt.showDecorationSelected = style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ShowDecorationSelected,
1759 opt: &opt, widget: this);
1760 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_PanelItemViewRow, opt: &opt, p: painter, w: this);
1761
1762 // draw background of the item (only alternate row). rest of the background
1763 // is provided by the delegate
1764 QStyle::State oldState = opt.state;
1765 opt.state &= ~QStyle::State_Selected;
1766 opt.rect.setRect(ax: reverse ? position : i + position, ay: y, aw: width - i, ah: height);
1767 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_PanelItemViewRow, opt: &opt, p: painter, w: this);
1768 opt.state = oldState;
1769 opt.showDecorationSelected = oldShowDecorationSelected;
1770
1771 if (d->indent != 0)
1772 drawBranches(painter, rect: branches, index);
1773 if (setClipRect)
1774 painter->restore();
1775 } else {
1776 QStyle::State oldState = opt.state;
1777 opt.state &= ~QStyle::State_Selected;
1778 opt.rect.setRect(ax: position, ay: y, aw: width, ah: height);
1779 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_PanelItemViewRow, opt: &opt, p: painter, w: this);
1780 opt.state = oldState;
1781 }
1782
1783 itemDelegateForIndex(index: modelIndex)->paint(painter, option: opt, index: modelIndex);
1784 }
1785
1786 if (currentRowHasFocus) {
1787 QStyleOptionFocusRect o;
1788 o.QStyleOption::operator=(other: option);
1789 o.state |= QStyle::State_KeyboardFocusChange;
1790 QPalette::ColorGroup cg = (option.state & QStyle::State_Enabled)
1791 ? QPalette::Normal : QPalette::Disabled;
1792 o.backgroundColor = option.palette.color(cg, cr: d->selectionModel->isSelected(index)
1793 ? QPalette::Highlight : QPalette::Window);
1794 int x = 0;
1795 if (!option.showDecorationSelected)
1796 x = header->sectionPosition(logicalIndex: 0) + d->indentationForItem(item: d->current);
1797 QRect focusRect(x - header->offset(), y, header->length() - x, height);
1798 o.rect = style()->visualRect(direction: layoutDirection(), boundingRect: d->viewport->rect(), logicalRect: focusRect);
1799 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_FrameFocusRect, opt: &o, p: painter);
1800 // if we show focus on all columns and the first section is moved,
1801 // we have to split the focus rect into two rects
1802 if (allColumnsShowFocus && !option.showDecorationSelected
1803 && header->sectionsMoved() && (header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: 0) != 0)) {
1804 QRect sectionRect(0, y, header->sectionPosition(logicalIndex: 0), height);
1805 o.rect = style()->visualRect(direction: layoutDirection(), boundingRect: d->viewport->rect(), logicalRect: sectionRect);
1806 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_FrameFocusRect, opt: &o, p: painter);
1807 }
1808 }
1809}
1810
1811/*!
1812 Draws the branches in the tree view on the same row as the model item
1813 \a index, using the \a painter given. The branches are drawn in the
1814 rectangle specified by \a rect.
1815*/
1816void QTreeView::drawBranches(QPainter *painter, const QRect &rect,
1817 const QModelIndex &index) const
1818{
1819 Q_D(const QTreeView);
1820 const bool reverse = isRightToLeft();
1821 const int indent = d->indent;
1822 const int outer = d->rootDecoration ? 0 : 1;
1823 const int item = d->current;
1824 const QTreeViewItem &viewItem = d->viewItems.at(i: item);
1825 int level = viewItem.level;
1826 QRect primitive(reverse ? rect.left() : rect.right() + 1, rect.top(), indent, rect.height());
1827
1828 QModelIndex parent = index.parent();
1829 QModelIndex current = parent;
1830 QModelIndex ancestor = current.parent();
1831
1832 QStyleOptionViewItem opt;
1833 initViewItemOption(option: &opt);
1834 QStyle::State extraFlags = QStyle::State_None;
1835 if (isEnabled())
1836 extraFlags |= QStyle::State_Enabled;
1837 if (hasFocus())
1838 extraFlags |= QStyle::State_Active;
1839 QPoint oldBO = painter->brushOrigin();
1840 if (verticalScrollMode() == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerPixel)
1841 painter->setBrushOrigin(QPoint(0, verticalOffset()));
1842
1843 if (d->alternatingColors) {
1844 opt.features.setFlag(flag: QStyleOptionViewItem::Alternate, on: d->current & 1);
1845 }
1846
1847 // When hovering over a row, pass State_Hover for painting the branch
1848 // indicators if it has the decoration (aka branch) selected.
1849 bool hoverRow = selectionBehavior() == QAbstractItemView::SelectRows
1850 && opt.showDecorationSelected
1851 && index.parent() == d->hover.parent()
1852 && index.row() == d->hover.row();
1853
1854 if (d->selectionModel->isSelected(index))
1855 extraFlags |= QStyle::State_Selected;
1856
1857 if (level >= outer) {
1858 // start with the innermost branch
1859 primitive.moveLeft(pos: reverse ? primitive.left() : primitive.left() - indent);
1860 opt.rect = primitive;
1861
1862 const bool expanded = viewItem.expanded;
1863 const bool children = viewItem.hasChildren;
1864 bool moreSiblings = viewItem.hasMoreSiblings;
1865
1866 opt.state = QStyle::State_Item | extraFlags
1867 | (moreSiblings ? QStyle::State_Sibling : QStyle::State_None)
1868 | (children ? QStyle::State_Children : QStyle::State_None)
1869 | (expanded ? QStyle::State_Open : QStyle::State_None);
1870 opt.state.setFlag(flag: QStyle::State_MouseOver, on: hoverRow || item == d->hoverBranch);
1871
1872 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_IndicatorBranch, opt: &opt, p: painter, w: this);
1873 }
1874 // then go out level by level
1875 for (--level; level >= outer; --level) { // we have already drawn the innermost branch
1876 primitive.moveLeft(pos: reverse ? primitive.left() + indent : primitive.left() - indent);
1877 opt.rect = primitive;
1878 opt.state = extraFlags;
1879 bool moreSiblings = false;
1880 if (d->hiddenIndexes.isEmpty()) {
1881 moreSiblings = (d->model->rowCount(parent: ancestor) - 1 > current.row());
1882 } else {
1883 int successor = item + viewItem.total + 1;
1884 while (successor < d->viewItems.size()
1885 && d->viewItems.at(i: successor).level >= uint(level)) {
1886 const QTreeViewItem &successorItem = d->viewItems.at(i: successor);
1887 if (successorItem.level == uint(level)) {
1888 moreSiblings = true;
1889 break;
1890 }
1891 successor += successorItem.total + 1;
1892 }
1893 }
1894 if (moreSiblings)
1895 opt.state |= QStyle::State_Sibling;
1896 opt.state.setFlag(flag: QStyle::State_MouseOver, on: hoverRow || item == d->hoverBranch);
1897
1898 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_IndicatorBranch, opt: &opt, p: painter, w: this);
1899 current = ancestor;
1900 ancestor = current.parent();
1901 }
1902 painter->setBrushOrigin(oldBO);
1903}

1936/*!
1937 \reimp
1938*/
1939void QTreeView::mouseDoubleClickEvent(QMouseEvent *event)
1940{
1941 Q_D(QTreeView);
1942 if (state() != NoState || !d->viewport->rect().contains(p: event->position().toPoint()))
1943 return;
1944
1945 int i = d->itemDecorationAt(pos: event->position().toPoint());
1946 if (i == -1) {
1947 i = d->itemAtCoordinate(coordinate: event->position().toPoint().y());
1948 if (i == -1)
1949 return; // user clicked outside the items
1950
1951 const QPersistentModelIndex firstColumnIndex = d->viewItems.at(i).index;
1952 const QPersistentModelIndex persistent = indexAt(p: event->position().toPoint());
1953
1954 if (d->pressedIndex != persistent) {
1955 mousePressEvent(event);
1956 return;
1957 }
1958
1959 // signal handlers may change the model
1960 emit doubleClicked(index: persistent);
1961
1962 if (!persistent.isValid())
1963 return;
1964
1965 if (edit(index: persistent, trigger: DoubleClicked, event) || state() != NoState)
1966 return; // the double click triggered editing
1967
1968 if (!style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ActivateItemOnSingleClick, opt: nullptr, widget: this))
1969 emit activated(index: persistent);
1970
1971 d->releaseFromDoubleClick = true;
1972 d->executePostedLayout(); // we need to make sure viewItems is updated
1973 if (d->itemsExpandable
1974 && d->expandsOnDoubleClick
1975 && d->hasVisibleChildren(parent: persistent)) {
1976 if (!((i < d->viewItems.size()) && (d->viewItems.at(i).index == firstColumnIndex))) {
1977 // find the new index of the item
1978 for (i = 0; i < d->viewItems.size(); ++i) {
1979 if (d->viewItems.at(i).index == firstColumnIndex)
1980 break;
1981 }
1982 if (i == d->viewItems.size())
1983 return;
1984 }
1985 if (d->viewItems.at(i).expanded)
1986 d->collapse(item: i, emitSignal: true);
1987 else
1988 d->expand(item: i, emitSignal: true);
1989 updateGeometries();
1990 viewport()->update();
1991 }
1992 }
1993}

2002 QAbstractItemView::mouseMoveEvent(event);

2005/*!
2006 \reimp
2007*/
2008void QTreeView::keyPressEvent(QKeyEvent *event)
2009{
2010 Q_D(QTreeView);
2011 QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
2012 //this is the management of the expansion
2013 if (d->isIndexValid(index: current) && d->model && d->itemsExpandable) {
2014 switch (event->key()) {
2015 case Qt::Key_Asterisk: {
2016 expandRecursively(index: current);
2017 break; }
2018 case Qt::Key_Plus:

2173/*!
2174 Move the cursor in the way described by \a cursorAction, using the
2175 information provided by the button \a modifiers.
2176*/
2177QModelIndex QTreeView::moveCursor(CursorAction cursorAction, Qt::KeyboardModifiers modifiers)
2178{
2179 Q_D(QTreeView);
2180 Q_UNUSED(modifiers);
2181
2182 d->executePostedLayout();
2183
2184 QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
2185 if (!current.isValid()) {
2186 int i = d->below(item: -1);
2187 int c = 0;
2188 while (c < d->header->count() && d->header->isSectionHidden(logicalIndex: d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: c)))
2189 ++c;
2190 if (i < d->viewItems.size() && c < d->header->count()) {
2191 return d->modelIndex(i, column: d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: c));
2192 }
2193 return QModelIndex();
2194 }
2195
2196 const int vi = qMax(a: 0, b: d->viewIndex(index: current));
2197
2198 if (isRightToLeft()) {
2199 if (cursorAction == MoveRight)
2200 cursorAction = MoveLeft;
2201 else if (cursorAction == MoveLeft)
2202 cursorAction = MoveRight;
2203 }
2204 switch (cursorAction) {
2205 case MoveNext:
2206 case MoveDown:
2207#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
2208 if (vi == d->viewItems.count()-1 && QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
2209 return d->model->index(0, current.column(), d->root);
2210#endif
2211 return d->modelIndex(i: d->below(item: vi), column: current.column());
2212 case MovePrevious:
2213 case MoveUp:
2214#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
2215 if (vi == 0 && QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
2216 return d->modelIndex(d->viewItems.count() - 1, current.column());
2217#endif
2218 return d->modelIndex(i: d->above(item: vi), column: current.column());
2219 case MoveLeft: {
2220 QScrollBar *sb = horizontalScrollBar();
2221 if (vi < d->viewItems.size() && d->viewItems.at(i: vi).expanded && d->itemsExpandable && sb->value() == sb->minimum()) {
2222 d->collapse(item: vi, emitSignal: true);
2223 d->moveCursorUpdatedView = true;
2224 } else {
2225 bool descend = style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ArrowKeysNavigateIntoChildren, opt: nullptr, widget: this);
2226 if (descend) {
2227 QModelIndex par = current.parent();
2228 if (par.isValid() && par != rootIndex())
2229 return par;
2230 else
2231 descend = false;
2232 }
2233 if (!descend) {
2234 if (d->selectionBehavior == SelectItems || d->selectionBehavior == SelectColumns) {
2235 int visualColumn = d->header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: current.column()) - 1;
2236 while (visualColumn >= 0 && isColumnHidden(column: d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: visualColumn)))
2237 visualColumn--;
2238 int newColumn = d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: visualColumn);
2239 QModelIndex next = current.sibling(arow: current.row(), acolumn: newColumn);
2240 if (next.isValid())
2241 return next;
2242 }
2243
2244 int oldValue = sb->value();
2245 sb->setValue(sb->value() - sb->singleStep());
2246 if (oldValue != sb->value())
2247 d->moveCursorUpdatedView = true;
2248 }
2249
2250 }
2251 updateGeometries();
2252 viewport()->update();
2253 break;
2254 }
2255 case MoveRight:
2256 if (vi < d->viewItems.size() && !d->viewItems.at(i: vi).expanded && d->itemsExpandable
2257 && d->hasVisibleChildren(parent: d->viewItems.at(i: vi).index)) {
2258 d->expand(item: vi, emitSignal: true);
2259 d->moveCursorUpdatedView = true;
2260 } else {
2261 bool descend = style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ArrowKeysNavigateIntoChildren, opt: nullptr, widget: this);
2262 if (descend) {
2263 QModelIndex idx = d->modelIndex(i: d->below(item: vi));
2264 if (idx.parent() == current)
2265 return idx;
2266 else
2267 descend = false;
2268 }
2269 if (!descend) {
2270 if (d->selectionBehavior == SelectItems || d->selectionBehavior == SelectColumns) {
2271 int visualColumn = d->header->visualIndex(logicalIndex: current.column()) + 1;
2272 while (visualColumn < d->model->columnCount(parent: current.parent()) && isColumnHidden(column: d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: visualColumn)))
2273 visualColumn++;
2274 const int newColumn = d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: visualColumn);
2275 const QModelIndex next = current.sibling(arow: current.row(), acolumn: newColumn);
2276 if (next.isValid())
2277 return next;
2278 }
2279
2280 //last restort: we change the scrollbar value
2281 QScrollBar *sb = horizontalScrollBar();
2282 int oldValue = sb->value();
2283 sb->setValue(sb->value() + sb->singleStep());
2284 if (oldValue != sb->value())
2285 d->moveCursorUpdatedView = true;
2286 }
2287 }
2288 updateGeometries();
2289 viewport()->update();
2290 break;
2291 case MovePageUp:
2292 return d->modelIndex(i: d->pageUp(item: vi), column: current.column());
2293 case MovePageDown:
2294 return d->modelIndex(i: d->pageDown(item: vi), column: current.column());
2295 case MoveHome:
2296 return d->modelIndex(i: d->itemForKeyHome(), column: current.column());
2297 case MoveEnd:
2298 return d->modelIndex(i: d->itemForKeyEnd(), column: current.column());
2299 }
2300 return current;

2303/*!
2304 Applies the selection \a command to the items in or touched by the
2305 rectangle, \a rect.
2306
2307 \sa selectionCommand()
2308*/
2309void QTreeView::setSelection(const QRect &rect, QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags command)
2310{
2311 Q_D(QTreeView);
2312 if (!selectionModel() || rect.isNull())
2313 return;
2314
2315 d->executePostedLayout();
2316 QPoint tl(isRightToLeft() ? qMax(a: rect.left(), b: rect.right())
2317 : qMin(a: rect.left(), b: rect.right()), qMin(a: rect.top(), b: rect.bottom()));
2318 QPoint br(isRightToLeft() ? qMin(a: rect.left(), b: rect.right()) :
2319 qMax(a: rect.left(), b: rect.right()), qMax(a: rect.top(), b: rect.bottom()));

2321 QModelIndex bottomRight = indexAt(point: br);
2322 if (!topLeft.isValid() && !bottomRight.isValid()) {
2323 if (command & QItemSelectionModel::Clear)
2324 selectionModel()->clear();

2326 }
2327 if (!topLeft.isValid() && !d->viewItems.isEmpty())
2328 topLeft = d->viewItems.constFirst().index;
2329 if (!bottomRight.isValid() && !d->viewItems.isEmpty()) {
2330 const int column = d->header->logicalIndex(visualIndex: d->header->count() - 1);
2331 const QModelIndex index = d->viewItems.constLast().index;
2332 bottomRight = index.sibling(arow: index.row(), acolumn: column);
2333 }
2334
2335 if (!d->isIndexEnabled(index: topLeft) || !d->isIndexEnabled(index: bottomRight))
2336 return;
2337
2338 d->select(start: topLeft, stop: bottomRight, command);

2341/*!
2342 Returns the rectangle from the viewport of the items in the given
2343 \a selection.
2344
2345 Since 4.7, the returned region only contains rectangles intersecting
2346 (or included in) the viewport.
2347*/
2348QRegion QTreeView::visualRegionForSelection(const QItemSelection &selection) const
2349{
2350 Q_D(const QTreeView);
2351 if (selection.isEmpty())
2352 return QRegion();
2353
2354 QRegion selectionRegion;
2355 const QRect &viewportRect = d->viewport->rect();
2356 for (const auto &range : selection) {
2357 if (!range.isValid())
2358 continue;
2359 QModelIndex parent = range.parent();
2360 QModelIndex leftIndex = range.topLeft();
2361 int columnCount = d->model->columnCount(parent);
2362 while (leftIndex.isValid() && isIndexHidden(index: leftIndex)) {
2363 if (leftIndex.column() + 1 < columnCount)
2364 leftIndex = d->model->index(row: leftIndex.row(), column: leftIndex.column() + 1, parent);
2365 else
2366 leftIndex = QModelIndex();
2367 }
2368 if (!leftIndex.isValid())
2369 continue;
2370 const QRect leftRect = visualRect(index: leftIndex);
2371 int top = leftRect.top();
2372 QModelIndex rightIndex = range.bottomRight();
2373 while (rightIndex.isValid() && isIndexHidden(index: rightIndex)) {
2374 if (rightIndex.column() - 1 >= 0)
2375 rightIndex = d->model->index(row: rightIndex.row(), column: rightIndex.column() - 1, parent);
2376 else
2377 rightIndex = QModelIndex();
2378 }
2379 if (!rightIndex.isValid())
2380 continue;
2381 const QRect rightRect = visualRect(index: rightIndex);
2382 int bottom = rightRect.bottom();
2383 if (top > bottom)
2384 qSwap<int>(value1&: top, value2&: bottom);
2385 int height = bottom - top + 1;
2386 if (d->header->sectionsMoved()) {
2387 for (int c = range.left(); c <= range.right(); ++c) {
2388 const QRect rangeRect(columnViewportPosition(column: c), top, columnWidth(column: c), height);
2389 if (viewportRect.intersects(r: rangeRect))
2390 selectionRegion += rangeRect;
2391 }
2392 } else {
2393 QRect combined = leftRect|rightRect;
2394 combined.setX(columnViewportPosition(column: isRightToLeft() ? range.right() : range.left()));
2395 if (viewportRect.intersects(r: combined))
2396 selectionRegion += combined;
2397 }
2398 }
2399 return selectionRegion;
2400}

2423/*!
2424 Scrolls the contents of the tree view by (\a dx, \a dy).
2425*/
2426void QTreeView::scrollContentsBy(int dx, int dy)
2427{
2428 Q_D(QTreeView);
2429
2430 d->delayedAutoScroll.stop(); // auto scroll was canceled by the user scrolling
2431
2432 dx = isRightToLeft() ? -dx : dx;
2433 if (dx) {
2434 int oldOffset = d->header->offset();
2435 d->header->d_func()->setScrollOffset(scrollBar: horizontalScrollBar(), scrollMode: horizontalScrollMode());
2436 if (horizontalScrollMode() == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerItem) {
2437 int newOffset = d->header->offset();
2438 dx = isRightToLeft() ? newOffset - oldOffset : oldOffset - newOffset;
2439 }
2440 }
2441
2442 const int itemHeight = d->defaultItemHeight <= 0 ? sizeHintForRow(row: 0) : d->defaultItemHeight;
2443 if (d->viewItems.isEmpty() || itemHeight == 0)
2444 return;
2445
2446 // guestimate the number of items in the viewport
2447 int viewCount = d->viewport->height() / itemHeight;
2448 int maxDeltaY = qMin(a: d->viewItems.size(), b: viewCount);
2449 // no need to do a lot of work if we are going to redraw the whole thing anyway
2450 if (qAbs(t: dy) > qAbs(t: maxDeltaY) && d->editorIndexHash.isEmpty()) {
2451 verticalScrollBar()->update();
2452 d->viewport->update();
2453 return;
2454 }
2455
2456 if (dy && verticalScrollMode() == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerItem) {
2457 int currentScrollbarValue = verticalScrollBar()->value();
2458 int previousScrollbarValue = currentScrollbarValue + dy; // -(-dy)
2459 int currentViewIndex = currentScrollbarValue; // the first visible item
2460 int previousViewIndex = previousScrollbarValue;
2461 dy = 0;
2462 if (previousViewIndex < currentViewIndex) { // scrolling down
2463 for (int i = previousViewIndex; i < currentViewIndex; ++i) {
2464 if (i < d->viewItems.size())
2465 dy -= d->itemHeight(item: i);
2466 }
2467 } else if (previousViewIndex > currentViewIndex) { // scrolling up
2468 for (int i = previousViewIndex - 1; i >= currentViewIndex; --i) {
2469 if (i < d->viewItems.size())
2470 dy += d->itemHeight(item: i);
2471 }
2472 }
2473 }
2474
2475 d->scrollContentsBy(dx, dy);
2476}

2496/*!
2497 Informs the view that the rows from the \a start row to the \a end row
2498 inclusive have been inserted into the \a parent model item.
2499*/
2500void QTreeView::rowsInserted(const QModelIndex &parent, int start, int end)
2501{
2502 Q_D(QTreeView);
2503 // if we are going to do a complete relayout anyway, there is no need to update
2504 if (d->delayedPendingLayout) {
2505 QAbstractItemView::rowsInserted(parent, start, end);
2506 return;
2507 }
2508
2509 //don't add a hierarchy on a column != 0
2510 if (parent.column() != 0 && parent.isValid()) {
2511 QAbstractItemView::rowsInserted(parent, start, end);
2512 return;
2513 }
2514
2515 const int parentRowCount = d->model->rowCount(parent);
2516 const int delta = end - start + 1;
2517 if (parent != d->root && !d->isIndexExpanded(idx: parent) && parentRowCount > delta) {
2518 QAbstractItemView::rowsInserted(parent, start, end);
2519 return;
2520 }
2521
2522 const int parentItem = d->viewIndex(index: parent);
2523 if (((parentItem != -1) && d->viewItems.at(i: parentItem).expanded)
2524 || (parent == d->root)) {
2525 d->doDelayedItemsLayout();
2526 } else if (parentItem != -1 && parentRowCount == delta) {
2527 // the parent just went from 0 children to more. update to re-paint the decoration
2528 d->viewItems[parentItem].hasChildren = true;
2529 viewport()->update();
2530 }
2531 QAbstractItemView::rowsInserted(parent, start, end);
2532}

2661/*!

2663 Expands all expandable items.
2664
2665 \note This function will not try to \l{QAbstractItemModel::fetchMore}{fetch more}
2666 data.
2667
2668 \warning If the model contains a large number of items,
2669 this function will take some time to execute.
2670
2671 \sa collapseAll(), expand(), collapse(), setExpanded()
2672*/
2673void QTreeView::expandAll()

2683/*!
2684 \since 5.13
2685 Expands the item at the given \a index and all its children to the
2686 given \a depth. The \a depth is relative to the given \a index.
2687 A \a depth of -1 will expand all children, a \a depth of 0 will
2688 only expand the given \a index.
2689
2690 \note This function will not try to \l{QAbstractItemModel::fetchMore}{fetch more}
2691 data.
2692
2693 \warning If the model contains a large number of items,
2694 this function will take some time to execute.
2695
2696 \sa expandAll()
2697*/
2698void QTreeView::expandRecursively(const QModelIndex &index, int depth)
2699{
2700 Q_D(QTreeView);
2701
2702 if (depth < -1)
2703 return;
2704 // do layouting only once after expanding is done
2705 d->doDelayedItemsLayout();
2706 expand(index);
2707 if (depth == 0)
2708 return;
2709 QStack<QPair<QModelIndex, int>> parents;
2710 parents.push(t: {index, 0});
2711 while (!parents.isEmpty()) {
2712 const QPair<QModelIndex, int> elem = parents.pop();
2713 const QModelIndex &parent = elem.first;
2714 const int curDepth = elem.second;
2715 const int rowCount = d->model->rowCount(parent);
2716 for (int row = 0; row < rowCount; ++row) {
2717 const QModelIndex child = d->model->index(row, column: 0, parent);
2718 if (!d->isIndexValid(index: child))
2719 break;
2720 if (depth == -1 || curDepth + 1 < depth)
2721 parents.push(t: {child, curDepth + 1});
2722 if (d->isIndexExpanded(idx: child))
2723 continue;
2724 if (d->storeExpanded(idx: child))
2725 emit expanded(index: child);
2726 }
2727 }
2728}

2847/*!
2848 Returns the size hint for the \a column's width or -1 if there is no
2849 model.
2850
2851 If you need to set the width of a given column to a fixed value, call
2852 QHeaderView::resizeSection() on the view's header.

2861int QTreeView::sizeHintForColumn(int column) const
2862{
2863 Q_D(const QTreeView);

2874
2875 int offset = 0;

2877 int end = d->lastVisibleItem(firstVisual: start, offset);
2878 if (start < 0 || end < 0 || end == viewItems.size() - 1) {
2879 end = viewItems.size() - 1;
2880 if (maximumProcessRows < 0) {
2881 start = 0;
2882 } else if (maximumProcessRows == 0) {
2883 start = qMax(a: 0, b: end - 1);
2884 int remainingHeight = viewport()->height();

2887 --start;

2889 } else {

2892 }
2893

2897 if (viewItems.at(i).spanning)
2898 continue; // we have no good size hint
2899 QModelIndex index = viewItems.at(i).index;
2900 index = index.sibling(arow: index.row(), acolumn: column);
2901 w = d->widthHintForIndex(index, hint: w, option, i);
2902 ++rowsProcessed;
2903 if (rowsProcessed == maximumProcessRows)
2904 break;
2905 }
2906
2907 --end;
2908 int actualBottom = viewItems.size() - 1;
2909
2910 if (maximumProcessRows == 0)
2911 rowsProcessed = 0; // skip the while loop
2912
2913 while (rowsProcessed != maximumProcessRows && (start > 0 || end < actualBottom)) {
2914 int idx = -1;
2915
2916 if ((rowsProcessed % 2 && start > 0) || end == actualBottom) {
2917 while (start > 0) {
2918 --start;
2919 if (viewItems.at(i: start).spanning)
2920 continue;
2921 idx = start;
2922 break;
2923 }
2924 } else {
2925 while (end < actualBottom) {

2927 if (viewItems.at(i: end).spanning)
2928 continue;
2929 idx = end;
2930 break;
2931 }
2932 }
2933 if (idx < 0)
2934 continue;
2935

2937 index = index.sibling(arow: index.row(), acolumn: column);

3323 //This can happen if columncount has been set to 0.
3324 //To avoid infinite loop we stop here.
3325 return;
3326 }
3327
3328 int count = 0;
3329 if (model->hasChildren(parent)) {
3330 if (model->canFetchMore(parent)) {
3331 // fetchMore first, otherwise we might not yet have any data for sizeHintForRow
3332 model->fetchMore(parent);
3333 // guestimate the number of items in the viewport, and fetch as many as might fit
3334 const int itemHeight = defaultItemHeight <= 0 ? q->sizeHintForRow(row: 0) : defaultItemHeight;
3335 const int viewCount = itemHeight ? viewport->height() / itemHeight : 0;
3336 int lastCount = -1;
3337 while ((count = model->rowCount(parent)) < viewCount &&
3338 count != lastCount && model->canFetchMore(parent)) {
3339 model->fetchMore(parent);
3340 lastCount = count;
3341 }
3342 } else {
3343 count = model->rowCount(parent);
3344 }
3345 }
3346
3347 bool expanding = true;
3348 if (i == -1) {
3349 if (uniformRowHeights) {
3350 QModelIndex index = model->index(row: 0, column: 0, parent);
3351 defaultItemHeight = q->indexRowSizeHint(index);
3352 }
3353 viewItems.resize(size: count);
3354 afterIsUninitialized = true;
3355 } else if (viewItems[i].total != (uint)count) {
3356 if (!afterIsUninitialized)
3357 insertViewItems(pos: i + 1, count, viewItem: QTreeViewItem()); // expand
3358 else if (count > 0)
3359 viewItems.resize(size: viewItems.size() + count);
3360 } else {
3361 expanding = false;
3362 }
3363
3364 int first = i + 1;
3365 int level = (i >= 0 ? viewItems.at(i).level + 1 : 0);
3366 int hidden = 0;
3367 int last = 0;
3368 int children = 0;
3369 QTreeViewItem *item = nullptr;
3370 for (int j = first; j < first + count; ++j) {
3371 current = model->index(row: j - first, column: 0, parent);
3372 if (isRowHidden(idx: current)) {
3373 ++hidden;
3374 last = j - hidden + children;
3375 } else {
3376 last = j - hidden + children;
3377 if (item)
3378 item->hasMoreSiblings = true;
3379 item = &viewItems[last];
3380 item->index = current;
3381 item->parentItem = i;
3382 item->level = level;
3383 item->height = 0;
3384 item->spanning = q->isFirstColumnSpanned(row: current.row(), parent);
3385 item->expanded = false;
3386 item->total = 0;
3387 item->hasMoreSiblings = false;
3388 if ((recursiveExpanding && !(current.flags() & Qt::ItemNeverHasChildren)) || isIndexExpanded(idx: current)) {
3389 if (recursiveExpanding && storeExpanded(idx: current) && !q->signalsBlocked())
3390 emit q->expanded(index: current);
3391 item->expanded = true;
3392 layout(i: last, recursiveExpanding, afterIsUninitialized);
3393 item = &viewItems[last];
3394 children += item->total;
3395 item->hasChildren = item->total > 0;
3396 last = j - hidden + children;
3397 } else {
3398 item->hasChildren = hasVisibleChildren(parent: current);
3399 }
3400 }
3401 }
3402
3403 // remove hidden items
3404 if (hidden > 0) {
3405 if (!afterIsUninitialized)
3406 removeViewItems(pos: last + 1, count: hidden);
3407 else
3408 viewItems.resize(size: viewItems.size() - hidden);
3409 }
3410
3411 if (!expanding)
3412 return; // nothing changed
3413
3414 while (i > -1) {
3415 viewItems[i].total += count - hidden;
3416 i = viewItems[i].parentItem;
3417 }
3418}

3489/*!
3490 \internal
3491 Returns the viewport y coordinate for \a item.
3492*/
3493int QTreeViewPrivate::coordinateForItem(int item) const
3494{
3495 if (verticalScrollMode == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerPixel) {
3496 if (uniformRowHeights)
3497 return (item * defaultItemHeight) - vbar->value();
3498 // ### optimize (maybe do like QHeaderView by letting items have startposition)
3499 int y = 0;
3500 for (int i = 0; i < viewItems.size(); ++i) {
3501 if (i == item)
3502 return y - vbar->value();
3503 y += itemHeight(item: i);
3504 }
3505 } else { // ScrollPerItem
3506 int topViewItemIndex = vbar->value();
3507 if (uniformRowHeights)
3508 return defaultItemHeight * (item - topViewItemIndex);
3509 if (item >= topViewItemIndex) {
3510 // search in the visible area first and continue down
3511 // ### slow if the item is not visible
3512 int viewItemCoordinate = 0;
3513 int viewItemIndex = topViewItemIndex;
3514 while (viewItemIndex < viewItems.size()) {
3515 if (viewItemIndex == item)
3516 return viewItemCoordinate;
3517 viewItemCoordinate += itemHeight(item: viewItemIndex);
3518 ++viewItemIndex;
3519 }
3520 // below the last item in the view
3521 Q_ASSERT(false);
3522 return viewItemCoordinate;
3523 } else {
3524 // search the area above the viewport (used for editor widgets)
3525 int viewItemCoordinate = 0;
3526 for (int viewItemIndex = topViewItemIndex; viewItemIndex > 0; --viewItemIndex) {
3527 if (viewItemIndex == item)
3528 return viewItemCoordinate;
3529 viewItemCoordinate -= itemHeight(item: viewItemIndex - 1);
3530 }
3531 return viewItemCoordinate;
3532 }
3533 }
3534 return 0;
3535}

3537/*!
3538 \internal
3539 Returns the index of the view item at the
3540 given viewport \a coordinate.
3541
3542 \sa modelIndex()
3543*/
3544int QTreeViewPrivate::itemAtCoordinate(int coordinate) const
3545{
3546 const int itemCount = viewItems.size();
3547 if (itemCount == 0)
3548 return -1;
3549 if (uniformRowHeights && defaultItemHeight <= 0)
3550 return -1;
3551 if (verticalScrollMode == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerPixel) {
3552 if (uniformRowHeights) {
3553 const int viewItemIndex = (coordinate + vbar->value()) / defaultItemHeight;
3554 return ((viewItemIndex >= itemCount || viewItemIndex < 0) ? -1 : viewItemIndex);
3555 }
3556 // ### optimize
3557 int viewItemCoordinate = 0;
3558 const int contentsCoordinate = coordinate + vbar->value();
3559 for (int viewItemIndex = 0; viewItemIndex < viewItems.size(); ++viewItemIndex) {
3560 viewItemCoordinate += itemHeight(item: viewItemIndex);
3561 if (viewItemCoordinate > contentsCoordinate)
3562 return (viewItemIndex >= itemCount ? -1 : viewItemIndex);
3563 }
3564 } else { // ScrollPerItem
3565 int topViewItemIndex = vbar->value();
3566 if (uniformRowHeights) {
3567 if (coordinate < 0)
3568 coordinate -= defaultItemHeight - 1;
3569 const int viewItemIndex = topViewItemIndex + (coordinate / defaultItemHeight);
3570 return ((viewItemIndex >= itemCount || viewItemIndex < 0) ? -1 : viewItemIndex);
3571 }
3572 if (coordinate >= 0) {
3573 // the coordinate is in or below the viewport
3574 int viewItemCoordinate = 0;
3575 for (int viewItemIndex = topViewItemIndex; viewItemIndex < viewItems.size(); ++viewItemIndex) {
3576 viewItemCoordinate += itemHeight(item: viewItemIndex);
3577 if (viewItemCoordinate > coordinate)
3578 return (viewItemIndex >= itemCount ? -1 : viewItemIndex);
3579 }
3580 } else {
3581 // the coordinate is above the viewport
3582 int viewItemCoordinate = 0;
3583 for (int viewItemIndex = topViewItemIndex; viewItemIndex >= 0; --viewItemIndex) {
3584 if (viewItemCoordinate <= coordinate)
3585 return (viewItemIndex >= itemCount ? -1 : viewItemIndex);
3586 viewItemCoordinate -= itemHeight(item: viewItemIndex);
3587 }
3588 }
3589 }
3590 return -1;
3591}

3593int QTreeViewPrivate::viewIndex(const QModelIndex &_index) const
3594{
3595 if (!_index.isValid() || viewItems.isEmpty())
3596 return -1;
3597
3598 const int totalCount = viewItems.size();
3599 const QModelIndex index = _index.sibling(arow: _index.row(), acolumn: 0);
3600 const int row = index.row();
3601 const quintptr internalId = index.internalId();
3602
3603 // We start nearest to the lastViewedItem
3604 int localCount = qMin(a: lastViewedItem - 1, b: totalCount - lastViewedItem);
3605 for (int i = 0; i < localCount; ++i) {
3606 const QModelIndex &idx1 = viewItems.at(i: lastViewedItem + i).index;
3607 if (idx1.row() == row && idx1.internalId() == internalId) {
3608 lastViewedItem = lastViewedItem + i;
3609 return lastViewedItem;
3610 }
3611 const QModelIndex &idx2 = viewItems.at(i: lastViewedItem - i - 1).index;
3612 if (idx2.row() == row && idx2.internalId() == internalId) {
3613 lastViewedItem = lastViewedItem - i - 1;
3614 return lastViewedItem;
3615 }
3616 }
3617
3618 for (int j = qMax(a: 0, b: lastViewedItem + localCount); j < totalCount; ++j) {
3619 const QModelIndex &idx = viewItems.at(i: j).index;
3620 if (idx.row() == row && idx.internalId() == internalId) {
3621 lastViewedItem = j;
3622 return j;
3623 }
3624 }
3625 for (int j = qMin(a: totalCount, b: lastViewedItem - localCount) - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
3626 const QModelIndex &idx = viewItems.at(i: j).index;
3627 if (idx.row() == row && idx.internalId() == internalId) {
3628 lastViewedItem = j;
3629 return j;
3630 }
3631 }
3632
3633 // nothing found
3634 return -1;
3635}

3648int QTreeViewPrivate::firstVisibleItem(int *offset) const
3649{
3650 const int value = vbar->value();
3651 if (verticalScrollMode == QAbstractItemView::ScrollPerItem) {
3652 if (offset)
3653 *offset = 0;
3654 return (value < 0 || value >= viewItems.size()) ? -1 : value;
3655 }
3656 // ScrollMode == ScrollPerPixel
3657 if (uniformRowHeights) {
3658 if (!defaultItemHeight)
3659 return -1;
3660
3661 if (offset)
3662 *offset = -(value % defaultItemHeight);
3663 return value / defaultItemHeight;
3664 }
3665 int y = 0; // ### (maybe do like QHeaderView by letting items have startposition)
3666 for (int i = 0; i < viewItems.size(); ++i) {
3667 y += itemHeight(item: i); // the height value is cached
3668 if (y > value) {
3669 if (offset)
3670 *offset = y - value - itemHeight(item: i);
3671 return i;
3672 }
3673 }
3674 return -1;
3675}

3677int QTreeViewPrivate::lastVisibleItem(int firstVisual, int offset) const
3678{

3680 firstVisual = firstVisibleItem(offset: &offset);
3681 if (firstVisual < 0)

3685 int value = viewport->height();
3686
3687 for (int i = firstVisual; i < viewItems.size(); ++i) {
3688 y += itemHeight(item: i); // the height value is cached
3689 if (y > value)
